summary: This document appears to be a certification form related to the opening of a bank account for a legal entity. It outlines the requirements for providing information about the beneficial owners and individuals with significant responsibility for managing the entity. The document emphasizes the need for accurate and complete information, including identification details for U.S. and non-U.S. persons.
keyFacts: The document requires the name and title of the natural person opening the account.
It specifies that individuals owning 25% or more of the legal entity must be identified.
The document includes provisions for U.S. and non-U.S. persons regarding identification requirements.
It mentions the need for a signature certifying the accuracy of the information provided.
The document is marked as confidential and is part of a larger set of records.
